This paper primarily focuses on the security and privacy aspects of the Bitcoin P2P network, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also involves modeling and analyzing the Bitcoin networking stack, which can be categorized under distributed systems (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the anonymity properties of the Bitcoin network, which can be related to the field of cryptography (cs.CY).
